Tue Feb 10 13:07:54 UTC 2026  Fred Hornsey  <hornseyf@objectcomputing.com>
        commit 52e1d58072b0432329acd2f920bdd3ba4616a5d9

        * dds/CMakeLists.txt:
        * dds/DCPS/ResizeSeqNoInit.h:
        * dds/idl/marshal_generator.cpp:

          Deserialize Primitive TAO Seqs Of Without Mem Init

          When sequences of primitives are deserialized, the generated code
          calls
          length before the elements are read in. The issue with length is
          it
          initializes the elements. This is wasted effort for primitives in
          this
          case because we read the number of elements from the CDR stream
          so
          unless the stream ends we know we're setting every element
          afterwards.
          In samples with large number of primitives setting the length
          (ultimately calling std::fill in TAO) can take up a significant
          amount
          of time.

